      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black Metallic. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure double VANOS system for optimized valve timing. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a tactile Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory limited-slip differential. This vehicle has undergone rigorous preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement and rear subframe reinforcement. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, supported by a precision-tuned suspension with Bilstein dampers. The interior is immaculate, featuring Nappa leather with no bolster wear, while the exterior retains its original factory luster. A mechanically peerless example for the serious collector.",
